# Chapter Writing Rules

Applies when editing files under `docs/`.

## Mandatory Section Order

Every chapter includes these 14 sections in order (see `STYLE_GUIDE.md`):

Learning Objectives → Prerequisites → Estimated Time → Background → Theory → Architecture → Walkthrough → Hands-on Lab → Verification → Troubleshooting → Review Questions → Key Takeaways → Glossary Additions → Further Reading

If a section does not apply, keep the header and explain why (e.g. Walkthrough N/A for conceptual chapters).

## Frontmatter (required)

```yaml
---
sidebar_position: N
description: "One-line summary for search/SEO."
---
```

## Hermes-Centric Framing

- Lead with what **Hermes** (the agent) needs from this topic
- Labs build toward running/operating the agent — not abstract exercises
- ULLR: integration context only; document API/auth/data from the agent's perspective
- Part VII folder is `docs/part-vii-hermes/` — titles use "Hermes agent," "agent tools," not "ULLR platform"

## Hermes Callout and Platform Status

**Every implementation chapter (Part II+)** must include:

1. At least one `:::note[Why this matters for Hermes]` admonition in Background or Theory
2. A **Hermes Platform Status** section before What's Next — update checkmarks and progress % (see `STYLE_GUIDE.md` template)
3. An **Engineering Decision Record** section linking to `code/infrastructure/edr/EDR-NNNN-*.md`

Part II chapter titles must be platform-first (e.g., "Provisioning Your AWS Account" not "AWS Overview").

## Guided Build — Three Layers

Implementation chapters (Part II+) follow **Concept → Design → Implementation**:

1. **Concept** (Background, opening Theory) — what problem are we solving?
2. **Design** (Architecture, tradeoffs in Theory) — why this approach for Hermes?
3. **Implementation** (Walkthrough, Lab) — exact AWS steps *after* layers 1–2

Never open the AWS console in Walkthrough until the reader understands why each resource exists.

## AWS Resource Naming

Use `hermes-` prefixed names: `hermes-vpc`, `hermes-public-usw2a`, `hermes-igw`, `hermes-public-rt`, `hermes-controlplane-sg`, `hermes-controlplane-01`. See `STYLE_GUIDE.md`.

## Infrastructure Artifacts

Each implementation chapter adds under `code/infrastructure/aws/`:

- `cloud-init/` — user-data scripts
- `cli/` — reproducible CLI / chapter scripts  
- `terraform/` — reserved until Part V
- `edr/` — Engineering Decision Records (see below)

Never commit `.pem` keys.

## Engineering Decision Records (EDR)

End each implementation chapter with an **Engineering Decision Record** section linking to `code/infrastructure/edr/EDR-NNNN-slug.md`. Format: Context, Decision, Consequences, Alternatives.

## Just-in-Time Linux

Do **not** require completing Chapter 3 Sections 3.4–3.7 before Part II. Teach `apt`, `journalctl`, `systemctl`, SSH, and `ufw` when the Hermes platform needs them (Ch 10, 12, Part III–IV). Sections 3.1–3.3 are sufficient to start building.

## Chapter 3 Structure (reference)

Sections 3.1–3.3 are core; 3.4–3.7 are reference / just-in-time:

| Section | Topic | When needed |
|---------|-------|-------------|
| 3.1 | Filesystem | Before Ch 7 |
| 3.2 | Users, groups, permissions | Before Ch 10 |
| 3.3 | Processes, systemd | Ch 12, Part IV |
| 3.4 | apt | Ch 12 |
| 3.5 | Networking tools + logs | Ch 8, 10 |
| 3.6 | SSH | Ch 10 |
| 3.7 | Capstone hardening | Ch 10 |

Readers may proceed to Chapter 6–7 after 3.3 if comfortable with a terminal.

## Labs

- Certification-guide format: Goal, Steps, Verification, Expected output, Troubleshooting, Cleanup
- Assets in `resources/labs/chNN/`
- Test commands before marking chapter done
- Never embed secrets

## Diagrams

- At least one diagram in Architecture
- Mermaid enabled via Docusaurus — use fenced `mermaid` blocks
- ASCII for network topology (≤80 cols)
- Store reusable sources in `resources/diagrams/`

## After Editing

1. Sync new glossary terms to `docs/appendices/glossary.md`
2. Update status in `SUMMARY.md` if RFC step completed
3. Run `npm run build` to catch broken links/anchors
4. Note entry in `CHANGELOG.md` for meaningful changes

## Internal Links

- Cross-chapter: `[Chapter 9](../part-ii-aws/09-provisioning-hermes-server.md)` (relative from current file)
- Same-chapter anchors must match Docusaurus slugified headings — verify with build
- Do not link to repo-root files (STYLE_GUIDE.md) from docs unless using full GitHub URL
